214. Shortest Palindrome
Solved
Hard
Topics
premium lock icon
Companies
You are given a string s. You can convert s to a palindrome by adding characters in front of it.

Return the shortest palindrome you can find by performing this transformation.

 

Example 1:

Input: s = "aacecaaa"
Output: "aaacecaaa"
Example 2:

Input: s = "abcd"
Output: "dcbabcd"
 

Constraints:

0 <= s.length <= 5 * 104
s consists of lowercase English letters only.

class Solution {
    public String shortestPalindrome(String s) {
        int l=0;
        int n=s.length();
        for(int r=n-1; r>=0;r--){
            if(s.charAt(l)==s.charAt(r)) {
                   l++;
            }
        }
        if(l==n)    return s;
        String nonpal=s.substring(l);
        String pal=s.substring(0,l);
        StringBuilder res=new StringBuilder(nonpal);
        return res.reverse().append(pal).toString();
    }
}
